The paper discusses the problem of representing the meaning of natural language utterances, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques to develop these representations (cs.AI, cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for new representations to address recent research needs, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) or software engineering (cs.SD).
